Key Match Events: Netherlands bowler Paul van Meekeren took 4 wickets for 23 runs.
Bas de Leede made a significant comeback by taking 2 wickets and running out Mahedi Hasan.
Scott Edwards scored an 89-ball 68, overcoming an edgy start.
Logan van Beek played a cameo of 23 not out from 16 balls.
Mustafizur Rahman took 2 wickets for 36 runs, including the crucial wicket of Wesley Barresi.
Shoriful Islam and Taskin Ahmed provided a strong start for Bangladesh by taking early wickets.
Pre-Game Insights: Bangladesh aimed to revive their campaign after losing four consecutive games.
Taskin Ahmed returned to the team after missing matches against India and South Africa due to a sore shoulder.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at Eden Gardens in Kolkata.
The Netherlands, an associate ICC member, now sit above defending champions England and Bangladesh in the points table.
Bangladesh fielders were not very sharp during the match.
